		<td colspan="2"><hr class="sep" /><div class="quotetitle">feos wrote:</div><div class="quotecontent">Here is a <a href="https://upload.wikimedia.org/wikipedia/commons/0/0d/PAL-NTSC-SECAM.svg" class="postlink">map of countries and video signal standards</a> used in them.</div><br />Which very misleadingly classifies Brazil as PAL, while PAL-M actually uses NTSC timing. Because this happened to my country in that map, I don't know how accurate it is for all other countries.<br /><br />BTW, I find it really amusing how pirates found a better way to make a PAL version of the NES/Famicom than Nintendo itself. I don't know if Nintendo intentionally made the PAL NES more different from the original than needed, as a form of region-locking, but judging by the many poor conversions that were made for the European market, I'm pretty sure that developers would've benefitted from better compatibility between the two systems.

		

		</td>
