	<tr>
		<td colspan="2"><hr class="sep" />Argentina (50Hz, 3.6MHz PAL) and Brazil (60Hz, 3.6MHz PAL) got their own special PPUs from UMC. Programs that run on Brazil's standard are definitely closer to 2C02 than UA6538.<br /><br />Comparisons of geography are misleading. Better comparisons would involve cartograms by population or ideally (and unavailable) by total numbers of relevant consoles (i.e. with a cart slot) sold.<br /><br />P.S. my page on the wiki: <a href="https://wiki.nesdev.com/w/index.php/User:Lidnariq/Known_PPU_revisions" class="postlink">nesdevwiki:User:Lidnariq/Known PPU revisions</a>

		

		</td>
	</tr>
	</table>


